
Overview of adj splendid

The adj splendid has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (7) glorious, resplendent, splendid, splendiferous -- (having great beauty and splendor; "a glorious spring morning"; "a glorious sunset"; "splendid costumes"; "a kind of splendiferous native simplicity")
2. excellent, first-class, fantabulous, splendid -- (very good;of the highest quality; "made an excellent speech"; "the school has excellent teachers"; "a first-class mind")
3. brilliant, glorious, magnificent, splendid -- (characterized by grandeur; "the brilliant court life at Versailles"; "a glorious work of art"; "magnificent cathedrals"; "the splendid coronation ceremony")
